the story behind anosmia perfumery I can&rsquo;t smell. No, it&rsquo;s not due to COVID; it&rsquo;s hereditary. No, I&rsquo;ve never been able to smell. Yes, I can still taste. This lack of olfactory sensation is called anosmia.
Anosmia is an invisible disability and, most of the time, it doesn&rsquo;t feel like a disability at all. Sure, I might accidentally have to spit out spoiled milk every now and again due to not realizing its state until after a taste, and sure, I frequently have to sniff something shoved under my nose out of politeness, but those experiences are mild inconveniences. In fact, I prefer not being bombarded with scents every minute of the day. I&rsquo;ve always found the culture around scents, perfumes, and colognes bizarre and excessive and I try my best to find unscented products.
